         <NarrativeTitle>Original Narrative</NarrativeTitle>
         <NarrativeText>&lt;span style="font-size:11pt"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:107%"&gt;&lt;span&gt;This incident was audibly and visually recorded using my Axon Body-Worn Camera, and MVA security cameras.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style="font-size:11pt"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:107%"&gt;&lt;span&gt;PHYSICAL EVIDENCE:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style="font-size:11pt"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:107%"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Two (2) digital photographs were taken of the victim&amp;rsquo;s injuries and four (4) digital photographs from surveillance video. The complete surveillance video was captured on DVD and placed in property at the MSP Forestville Barrack.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style="font-size:11pt"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:107%"&gt;&lt;span&gt;OFFICER EXPERIENCE:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style="font-size:11pt"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:107%"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; I, TFC R. Backus #6648, am a sworn police officer currently assigned to uniformed patrol with the Maryland State Police, Prince Frederick Barrack, located at 210 Main Street, Prince Frederick, Calvert County, Maryland. I have more than 7 years of law enforcement training and experience conducting Criminal and Controlled Dangerous Substance (CDS) investigations, and CDS detection while on uniformed patrol. I received training in the laws pertaining to Constitutional Law, including, but not limited to, the laws pertaining to Search and Seizure. I have arrested and participated in the successful prosecution of several individuals for violating Maryland&amp;rsquo;s Criminal laws in both the District and Circuit Courts of Calvert County, Maryland. I have testified in cases before the District and Circuit Courts of Calvert County, Maryland, leading to the conviction of the defendants. Through all of this training and experience, I am familiar with different variations of the use, packaging, and distribution of Controlled Dangerous Substances. I have also conducted countless traffic stop roadside interviews. That accumulative experience, as well as my training, grants me the ability to recognize criminal indicators, nervousness, and signs of deception during brief personal contacts. I know that signs of deception and nervous behavior tends to be present when someone is trying to conceal their involvement in criminal activity. I know that my observations, as a totality of circumstances, can establish a reasonable articulable suspicion that criminal activity is present.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style="font-size:11pt"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:107%"&gt;&lt;span&gt;NARRATIVE:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style="font-size:11pt"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:107%"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; On April 10, 2023, at approximately 1145 hours, I was on duty at the Largo Maryland Motor Vehicle Administration (MVA) building, along with Cpl. D. Taylor #5479. I was alerted to a physical altercation that occurred between MVA employee, Tina Ladene Pugh (W/F DOB 2/18/1968) and a Melanie Drummond (B/F DOB 10/5/1980). &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style="font-size:11pt"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:107%"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; I made contact with Drummond as she was attempting to leave the premises. Drummond complied with the order to stop and was escorted along with her child to an interview room. Review of the MVA security camera footage showed Pugh was seated on behind one of the work stations. Drummond approached Pugh from the customer side of the work station, reached over the top of the plastic barrier and struck Pugh on the side of her face.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;While speaking with Drummond, she became very emotional and repeated &amp;ldquo;she was nasty&amp;rdquo; and then became apologetic. I detected the odor of an alcoholic beverage emitting from Drummond&amp;rsquo;s breath and person. I offered Drummond a preliminary breath test but was refused.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style="font-size:11pt"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:107%"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; While speaking with Drummond, Cpl. Taylor and I were alerted to another customer at the MVA who possibly had a warrant for her arrest. I contacted the MSP College Park barrack to request another Trooper respond to assist however none was available at that time.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style="font-size:11pt"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:107%"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Drummond was issued DC-45 Uniform Criminal Citations for the following:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style="font-size:11pt"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:107%"&gt;&lt;span&gt;1 1415, CR 3-203, Second Degree Assault.(122002720766)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style="font-size:11pt"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:107%"&gt;&lt;span&gt;2 0050, CR 10-201(C) (3), Disorderly Conduct. (122002720770)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style="font-size:11pt"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:107%"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Drummond was advised she was banned from the MVA Largo location, and she would need to go to another MVA location in the future. Drummond was advised that after leaving the premises if she returned to the MVA Largo location she would be placed under arrest for trespassing. Drummond was released with all of her appropriate paperwork.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style="font-size:11pt"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:107%"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Pugh provided and handwritten statement, provided with a victim/witness pamphlet, and advised of the peace/protective order process.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; On 5/15/2023, I received notification from the MVA Police that an official copy of the video footage of the incident had been sent to me by Federal Express. After reviewing the surveillance video, four (4) digital photographs were captured and uploaded to this report.&amp;nbsp;The complete surveillance video was captured on DVD and placed in property at the MSP Forestville Barrack.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style="font-size:11pt"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:107%"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Case closed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style="font-size:11pt"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:107%"&gt;&lt;span&gt;All events occurred in Prince George&amp;#39;s County, Maryland&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &amp;nbsp;</NarrativeText>
